dcterms:description: A novel dataset created for assessing the quality of Java code, consisting of programming solutions for a JavaFX task completed by 250 students, which corresponds to more than 25,000 Java methods. Domain experts assign a score based on the methods' intrinsic quality, representing subjective qualities such as elegance, readability, and succinctness.
dcterms:title: Novel dataset for code quality assessment

dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of 200,000 Java methods downloaded from GitHub repositories tagged with JavaFX, used for domain-adapted pre-training of the CodeBERT model.
dcterms:title: Java methods dataset from GitHub

dcterms:description: A task-adapted dataset containing 10,000 Java methods from previous years' JavaFX assignments, used for task-adapted pre-training of the CodeBERT model.
dcterms:title: Task-adapted dataset

dcterms:description: A dataset of programming solutions for a JavaFX task completed by 250 students, which corresponds to more than 25,000 Java methods, used to assess the quality of programming assignments.
dcterms:title: Dataset of programming solutions for a JavaFX task
